First off the price is certainly right so .... 'IF' these socks fit your feet and are comfortable ... they are a good value.

I found this socks to be lightweight and thin. Unfortunately for me, these socks didn't fit and were not comfortable. Thanks to Amazon's "Free Return" policy I was able to send these socks back and buy something different

reviews:
One wash later. ONE.

I’ve never had this issue with socks in my life.
Too bad, as they felt great when new.
Ripoff.
Never again!
product_name: Dickies Men's Dri-tech Moisture Control Crew Socks Multipack

reviews: I've been searching for 2 years to find socks that actually fit my huge and mangled feet. Three times on Amazon I've ordered socks that promised to fit my 13EEEE feet and three times I had to return them. These arrived today and it was with much trepidation that I tried them on. Wow. They fit and they are comfortable. I was so impressed I immediately ordered 3 more. My previous socks were getting to be religious icons (holy). I bought those 2 years before my near fatal accident left me with huge and mangled feet. Thank you so much
product_name: Dickies Men's Dri-tech Moisture Control Crew Socks Multipack

reviews: Had a hard time finding socks to fit my size 13 wide feet until I came across these Dickies. I wear them to work and have lasted a long time. product_name: Dickies Men's Dri-tech Moisture Control Crew Socks Multipack

reviews: It seems silly to review socks, but my biggest question before ordering these was thickness. I wear a casual Oxford shoe and jeans to work. Dress socks are too thin, and work socks too thick. I'm really happy with the thickness of these. They are a bit thinner than socks I've traditionally worn, but still much thicker than a dress sock. I'm really happy with the thickness. Other than that, time will tell. New, they feel good and are comfortable at the calf. I won't know for some time how they wear at the heal or how the elastic holds up, but they're socks. Eventually the heal will tear or the elastic will fade. Then you get new ones... right? They're socks. Oh yeah, they're socks with the Dickies brand across the toe... for those who care about such things. Good luck with your investment... (can't believe I just wrote a review for socks)
product_name: Dickies Men's Dri-tech Moisture Control Crew Socks Multipack

reviews:
Je travaille de la maison. Pour des raisons de confort et de préférence, je marche presque toujours sur mes bas. Je change de bas tous les jours, effectuant une bonne rotations. Après seulement 6 semaines, j'ai déjà 2 bas percés sous la plante du pied. A titre comparatif, sous le même traitement, les autres marques de bas durent facilement plus de 6 mois.

Les bas sont tout de même confortable. Si vous ne marché pas régulièrement sur vos bas, l'usure sera moins rapide et il est possible que ces bas puissent vous convenir.

See picture where sock on top is fresh put of dryer while bottom sock is after 12 hours of normal walking/standing/sitting. As you can see it is noticeably bigger/looser, but not horrible.

review_title: Just Not What I Was Expecting
reviews:
I ended up returning these as they just weren't what I was expecting. I recently started buying high quality merino wool socks and I guess perhaps I was just too used to how they feel compared to this synthetic, somewhat cheap feeling material. And even though I bought the 12-15 shoe sized socks, they did not fit me well, nor did they come up my leg to what I felt a "crew" shock should, or I guess what I have become accustomed to with these other higher quality wool socks.

They did arrive on time, and the return of them was painless, which I appreciated, but they just weren't for me, nor what I was looking for. They may be fine for you, and Dickies has always been a decent brand for me in the past, but just not my cup of tea when it came to these socks. I gave them 3 stars only because they're not for me. I have nothing to complain about as far as the delivery, return, or the quality of them, just not for me.
product_name: Dickies Men's Dri-tech Moisture Control Crew Socks Multipack

reviews:

reviews:

Do t think too hard about this one. Just get them for casual socks.
product_name: Dickies Men's Dri-tech Moisture Control Crew Socks Multipack

reviews:

These aren't too thick to make my feet sweat at the office, but not too thin that I think they will rip any second. Wore them all day and they didn't seem to smell, and I can't comment on the arch support.

Overall, very happy about the size, thickness, and price for the number of pairs.

reviews: I used this product on my feet. review_title: Dri-Tech Crew: Cotton content, wicking ability, and pilling
reviews:
Overall, very good socks.
Dickies' dri-tech crew socks that I received have the following fibre content:
56% cotton, 41% polyester, 2% spandex, and 1% nylon (photo provided)
As others in the comments/questions have pointed out, this affects the comfort and wicking ability of the sock.
I found the socks wick decently when I am walking and hiking while still being comfortable.
After 4 sets of use and washing/drying cycles, there is only very minor amounts of pilling (so far)
I would purchase these again.
product_name: Dickies Men's Dri-tech Moisture Control Crew Socks Multipack

reviews: This are the bomb: comfortable, not too long in the crotch area, thick enough to take them out but not too thick to be winterwear only. They're not truly black though, closer to a very dark charcoal/gray. Here is a picture of them compared to Mark's leggings (which are both very black and thick). Pictures taken on different lightings for illustrative purposes. This have a smaller waistband, more for comfort than tummy control.
product_name: Hanes Womens Stretch Jersey Legging Leggings

reviews:
These leggings are very comfortable. The main issue with them is that they are a little sheer and do not pass the squat test. I ordered the black ones in XL and when I was squatting, I could totally see the polka dots on my underwear. It's not like they were overly stretched over my butt either, the leggings had room to spare.
I think you can avoid this if you wear solid dark underwear, without any motifs. They are also very long for me, I am 5'3 and they bunch up at my ankles. I will have to hem them, but that's a problem that I have with most leggings.
I am going to keep them for lounging around the house and wearing them under tunics, so these issues do not bother me too much. Just beware if you're looking for a pair of opaque leggings, these ain't it.
product_name: Hanes Womens Stretch Jersey Legging Leggings

reviews: Not sure if it's the fabric or what, but these are THE most uncomfortable leggings I've every owned. They seem to have no "give", so even though they fit - they don't. They're just irritating to wear. They're also not a good idea for anyone with pets, or with family, friends or acquaintances, with pets as they seem to be a magnet for every bit of lint, hair, etc. in the vicinity. I could not, in good faith recommend these and won't be buying them again.
product_name: Hanes Womens Stretch Jersey Legging Leggings

reviews: So I ordered black leggings, and they fit pretty good, although I would say that for people with normal length legs these would be a bit on the short side. I have short stubby legs, so that wasn't a problem, however, the colour is - they are definitely a dark brown. When I go to wear them with anything black, I look like a bruise, but if I put them on with anything brown - they're just a little too black. I figure a few more washes will fix the latter problem. They're fading each time I launder them. So overall, decent price but don't purchase if you want a colour fast dye (or have long legs).
product_name: Hanes Womens Stretch Jersey Legging Leggings

product_name: Hanes Womens Stretch Jersey Legging Leggings

review_title: Constantly pulling up, cheap, baggy, DONT BUY (plus sizes available)
reviews:
Plus sizes available. I'm on the larger end of 1x (sizes 16-18), I'm 5'2", between 185-200 lbs, and these fit me. Super cheap jersey knit leggings, comfy with good coverage (not sheer), but like other reviews have mentioned these DO STRETCH OUT A LOT!!!!!! I wanted to ignore the reviews because I needed something inexpensive, but these lived up to the bad reviews. Don't buy them.
When I first put them on in the morning I feel secure and feel like they fit well for a few minutes, but then throughout the day find myself constantly trying to pull them up because they constantly feel like they're falling down and off my butt!!!
Maybe a size down would help? But they're not super thick so you'd run the chances of them being stretched sheer in a smaller size. I've relegated these to sleep wear only because feeling like they're constantly dragging down doesn't make me feel very confident or secure.
product_name: Hanes Womens Stretch Jersey Legging Leggings

reviews: Love these leggings, they're very comfy & easy to put on. The fabric doesn't tear easy & they're opaque so you don't have to worry about exposing yourself wearing these. I've worn leggings that were supposedly opaque but they still showed everything...these are good & come in different colours.

reviews: I have been buying these socks for more than 20 years for my husband. Sometimes from Costco sometimes from amazon. Up unto this year I have obviously been satisfied however the last 2 packs have all developed a hole in the heel within 3 weeks of purchase. My employer said he had the same issue which made me feel bad as I had recommended them. I am so disappointed and unfortunately will no longer be recommending or purchasing
product_name: Champion Men's 6 Pack High Performance Crew Sock

reviews: These socks are comfortable and were a decent price on sale, but I definitely expected more. One sock came apart at the big toe after only being worn twice. Probably wouldn't buy again, I had hoped for a mid-range sock for a good price, but feel like I got a really cheap sock for a near mid-range price. Updated - more have fallen apart, now I feel like I got garbage for the price of a mid quality sock. Will never purchase again. Brings down the name of Champion and Hanes.
product_name: Champion Men's 6 Pack High Performance Crew Sock

review_title: One sock out of the six was extremely frayed and unwearable
reviews: My husband has always worn these ‘Champion’ socks and never had an issue. This was the first time purchasing them online, usually we buy them at Sportchecknor Costco. Five and a half of the six socks were perfect but one single sock was so frayed inside and out that it was unwearable. Otherwise would have given five stars instead of three.
product_name: Champion Men's 6 Pack High Performance Crew Sock

reviews: These are the only socks my husband will wear now. They a not so long as to reach his knees, but they rest just perfectly mid-calf. They wash nice, wear nice, and last a long time. Well worth the money. We have purchased these socks before at Costco and Wal-mart, but neither store near us carries them anymore. So glad I found them on amazon!
product_name: Champion Men's 6 Pack High Performance Crew Sock

reviews:
Purchased for my teenage boy’s and husband

They love them.
Super durable w the enforced grey bottoms.
Breathable amd doesn’t leave feet sweaty and smelly.
Very good quality and a very reasonable cost for the quality and amount of socks you get
product_name: Champion Men's 6 Pack High Performance Crew Sock

reviews:
Since the new design I have noticed my champion socks are tearing at the grey design lines on the sole.

These socks used to last for quite a time, a year at least, most often much longer tho. The first image shows the solid grey sole of an old design champion sock, along side the new grey slash pattern socks.

I have had the new design socks for less than 3 months and they are all falling apart already. All of them at the same time too, and right along the grey lines on the sole. I can actually tear the sock along the grey fabric perfectly.

Very poor design Hanes. Like others, I have to wonder if this is intentional tho. It is clearly weaker material around these new grey design lines that are situated on the part of the sock that will receive the highest wear, the sole, as seen in the second picture. Very disappointing.

I would not suggest these for purchase as they are not cheap, and now they only last a few months before completely disintegrating.

reviews: Purchased this set thinking it was a good deal however after one wear of several items within this set our baby got some stains on them and after 7-8 washes, using 3-4 different stain removers the stains are still there, have never had this issue before with baby clothing, I am usually able to get stains out, even really tough stains out within 1-2 washes, we have probably spent more on stain removers than we did for this set. We have had to throw out 3 of the pieces from this set. Very disappointed, we really only got 1 wear each of the 3 items and that was it. Not worth the money or the amount of tme you will spend trying to get stains out, spend a little more money and get some quality clothing for your child, every baby & child will get things dirty, so just be aware. I totally regret this purchase.

reviews: The material is super breezy and soft, making it a perfect piece for summer! I love that it's a stretch viscose with absolutely no polyester content (I can't even begin to describe how much I hate polyester). It's very flattering. Thank you to other reviewers who said to size down! I am normally a size XL but I went for the L and it fit perfectly! I am 5ft 2in and the dress *just* sweeps the floor. I'm okay with the length but anyone shorter than me would either trip over the dress constantly or need it hemmed. I bought both the black and the charcoal grey but am returning the grey because it doesn't look as pulled together. Can't beat the price! Would love to see Amazon make them in more colours and maybe consider some patterned fabric to the skirt with a plain black bodice!
product_name: Amazon Essentials Women's Surplice Maxi Dress

reviews: I would say it's great for casual summer events. It looks nice but is a "cheaper" feeling material and stitching. The fabric is a jersey type material that feels nice and is very stretchy. I bought this to wear home from the hospital when I have my baby in a couple of weeks. I find it clings a bit more than I was hoping but it will be easy to put on and not tight on the tummy at all. I also liked the top because it's great for breastfeeding. I usually wear a medium now but ordered a small in this and I'm glad I did. It's comfortable now but when I lose the baby weight it will have a looser, more flowing look. I'm happy overall!
product_name: Amazon Essentials Women's Surplice Maxi Dress

reviews: even though i was sent the wrong dress the first time, amazon.ca made it right. the customer service was well above any i have ever received before. now for the dress: its super soft. comfortable to wear . a little long on me but as im 5' i exspected it to be. anyone over 5'2" would be fine. it flows when you move but isnt overly heavy. i can wear it now in the summer as a quick dressy dress with some classic jewerly. and im sure with a cardigan it will look nice all through the fall. it will be a staple in my travel bag. can be wore over a swimsuit as a cover up or out to dinner. easy to walk in. price for value is a bonus. i may buy one for my daughter for work. i cant say enough good things about this dress.
product_name: Amazon Essentials Women's Surplice Maxi Dress

reviews: Fabric is very soft. Not see through. SUPER comfortable. It is a little looser than I imagined so it’s not very flattering. I thought about going down a size but it’s so comfy the way it is I left it. I’m 5’8” 145lbs and got a size medium. It stays closed on the chest area so you don’t have to worry about too much boob. Dress sits just above my ankles.
product_name: Amazon Essentials Women's Surplice Maxi Dress

reviews: I’m 5’6” and about 200lbs and the L fits me perfectly. I normally wear an XL but am a bit smaller in the shoulders so went down a size based on reviews. The length is perfect and might be silly for anyone taller. I do find it shows a bit more cleavage than I’d like (I’m an H cup) but I plan to just pin it at the chest. Overall it’s soft and light and a great casual option for hot days, just what I was looking for!
product_name: Amazon Essentials Women's Surplice Maxi Dress

reviews: This dress is soft like a perfect t-shirt. It hangs beautifully. It covers the tummy bulge area nicely. It is very simple, and very plain. I am going to add a small pin to keep the top shut and make it not quite so plain. The top would be ok I think as long as you didn't lean over. I just will put the pin there, and possibly a stitch, so that I don't have to think about it. I'm 5'5" and slightly overweight. It looks nice enough to wear to a restaurant, or just out for a walk.
product_name: Amazon Essentials Women's Surplice Maxi Dress

reviews: I am always skeptical about buying clothing on amazon but this dress is beautiful. Material is soft and overall it seems to be good quality. I am 5'2 and weigh about 170lbs and the large fit perfectly as the material has good stretch to it (I'm glad I didn't go with the XL like I had originally planned). May have to get it hemmed an inch but if you're over 5'2 it shouldn't be a problem. Definetly recommend!

review_title: Comfortable but not a very thick sweatshirt
reviews:
Product arrived on time (as per guarantee delivery date)
A bit tough to review the fit as I am a female...usually I wear a mens medium comfortably to accommodate my wide set shoulders, But I think I could actually go to a small in this one as the medium is quite baggy.
I also have a short torso (i am 5'2) but the length is perfect for me.

Comfortable. Thinner than I expected but might actually be better for layering.

Bought the charcoal grey, color matches picture.

I will definitely buy another (or 2!) but perhaps size down to see if its a better fit.

Its cozy and i cant complain about the price

EDIT: When checking the size chart - my chest measurement bumps me into the "large" size....so for me, sizing is extremely inaccurate I am swimming a bit in the Medium!
product_name: Fruit of the Loom Men's Hooded Sweatshirt
brand_name: Fruit of the Loom Mens Athletic

reviews: I really love this sweater. It’s well made, there no loose threads hanging on it, or any weird stitching or anything. It’s very sturdy and I have no doubt it will last for a long time. I also really like how soft it is on the inside, it makes it super cozy to wear, and the color is what was pictured and what I wanted. The only thing that isn’t my favourite is I wish it was a bit thicker. It’s not overly thin or anything but I do prefer nice heavy warm sweaters. Overall I would definitely reccomend this sweater though :)

review_title: Un cadeau que mon homme apprécie
reviews:
J'ai acheté ce chandail comme cadeau de la part de mon fils à mon mari, pour la Fête des pères. Le tissu est de très bonne qualité et est parfaitement ajusté. De plus, il ne décolore pas au lavage. Les couleurs sont belles et contrastantes.

Comme mon conjoint travaille dans la construction, il a reçu beaucoup de compliments de la part de collègues qui en voulaient un eux, aussi. On rit à chaque fois qu'il le porte à la maison car si papa ne peut réparer quelque chose, comme il est écrit sur le chandail, on est réellement mal pris comme il est écrit. :)
product_name: If PAPA Can't Fix It We're All Screwed Gift for Grandpa Dad T-Shirt

reviews: I'm glad I read the reviews where some people said the shirt fit a little big. I got a Medium for my dad and I think it'll fit well. When I took it out of the package I was a little shocked at how large the words were. In the picture they look to take up about 3/4 of the shirt maybe a little less. The one I got takes up the entire shirt. The drill is huge! I did post a pic it's on the back on my chair at work so hopefully you can see what I mean about the design. Overall the shirt feels nice and it'll be fine for something else to wear in his shop. Also I didn't receive a card or anything else that some people said they did.
product_name: If PAPA Can't Fix It We're All Screwed Gift for Grandpa Dad T-Shirt

reviews: I'm really disappointed. I took X-LARGE and it seems more like an XXL-LARGE + the delivery took longer than expected so I don't have the time to change it before fathers day. I live in the same town as friend who ordered the same day as me and she received the t-shirt on time but my delivery took 2 weeks longer to arrive...
product_name: If PAPA Can't Fix It We're All Screwed Gift for Grandpa Dad T-Shirt
